bally.Based on new research, Capital and popular cinema will be of interest to undergraduate and post-graduate students, researchers and scholars of cult and exploitation cinema, genre cinema, national cinema, film and media theory, and area studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCult films--History and criticism. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aIndian cinema.  aItalian cinema.  aMexican cinema.  aaesthetics.  acomparative film studies.  aeconomy.  afilm genres.  ahorror film.  amodes of address.  a‹i›giallo‹/i›.1 aVitali, Valentina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499733540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784997335423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784997335/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles